<br>
<font color=yellow>When Jesus requests that we love our neighbors does that include abortionists and homosexuals? In some people's minds yes in others acceptance of them is a sin in itself. Which group is sinning? Those who propogate hate in the name of God or those who support immorality in the name of God. The answer depends on your interpretation. The true problem however, comes when forcing your personal interpretation onto others.</font color><br>
<br>
Okay define love.  It says to love them, doesn't say you have to like them.  I know its symantics but love carries a stronger conotation of action.  Treat them right.  I know this because it says to love your enemies... now if you like them then they aren't your enemies are they?  <br>
<br>
Even beyond that however I don't hate or dislike homosexuals.  I simply hate what they do.  I am sure you have heard "hate the sin not the sinner,"  or  "love the sinner, hate the sin" or other similar cliches.  Abortionists is the same thing.<br>
<br>
If someone is born with attraction to the same sex they are not a sinner.  If, however, they act on it... they are.  It is possible to resist temptation.  Its not a popular view but then people aren't really gonna like hell either.  I have talked to people who are attracted to men but respect God's plan.  They say its not easy.  I believe them.<br>
